. Entsprechend stehen in zahlreichen Beiträgen rezeptionsgeschichtliche Fragestellungen im Mittelpunkt, die einen Zeitraum von der archaischen Dichtung Roms bis in die frühe Neuzeit umfassen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDrama. 4aLatein. 4aRömisches Reich. 4aTheater. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aBlänsdorf, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlänsdorf, Jürgen.1 aDeufert, Marcus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeufert, Marcus.1 aFugmann, Joachim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJanka, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanka, Markus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJanka, Markus.1 aKlein, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Richard.1 aMoreschini, Claudio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreschini, Claudio.1 aSchmitzer, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitzer, Ulrich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchmitzer, Ulrich.1 aSeng, Helmut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeismann, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeismann, Werner.1 aZimmermann, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimmermann, Bernhard.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN0 cprintz978359873019140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092885340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110928853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110928853/original  aEBA_BACKALL